  "prompt": "Can I put a sleep number matress on a platform frame?",
  "response": "Yes, you can place a Sleep Number mattress on a platform frame, but there are a few important considerations to ensure proper support and optimal performance of the mattress:\n\n1. **Flat and Solid Surface**: Sleep Number mattresses require a flat, solid, and even surface for proper support. A platform frame that has slats should have slats spaced no more than 2 inches apart to prevent sagging or damage to the mattress.\n\n2. **No Box Spring Needed**: Platform frames are designed to support mattresses directly, so you do not need a box spring with a Sleep Number mattress.\n\n3. **Weight Capacity**: Ensure the platform frame can support the combined weight of the mattress, the Sleep Number base (if you\u2019re using one), and the sleepers. Sleep Number mattresses and bases can be heavy, especially with adjustable models.\n\n4. **Adjusted if Using Sleep Number Base**: If you\u2019re using a Sleep Number adjustable base, you\u2019ll need to make sure the platform frame can accommodate its height and movement if it\u2019s a moving/flexing base.\n\n5. **Headboard and Footboard Compatibility**: If your platform frame includes a headboard or footboard, ensure it is compatible with the mattress thickness and any additional height from the base.\n\nIf you\u2019re unsure, Sleep Number\u2019s customer service or the manufacturer of your platform frame can provide guidance. Always follow the manufacturer\u2019s recommendations for your specific mattress and frame.",
